pf|y|NT|^B@2|cp|8|at|
hondo717: |cp||at|The other point on this hand is the  ways to show blackwood with a void.
1) A 5N response shows an even number of key cards (0, 2, or 4) and a void.
2) 6 of a suit shows an odd number of key cards (1 or 3) and a void in the suit bid. If the suit is above the trump suit (as in this case, where trumps are diamonds and the void is in hearts), then 6 of the trump suit shows a void in a higher ranking suit. (Had the void been in clubs, responder would bid 6 clubs).|
PG| ***** 64 ***** |


PF|Y|NT|^B@2|cp|8|at|
hondo717: |cp||at|Note that the void should be "useful", meaning that it is probably not in a suit where the RKCB bidder has shown cards. In this case, the heart void is probably not useful, since the RKCB bidder showed hearts, so on this hand, I would not bid 5N (showing 2 key cards and a void), but 5H (showing 2 key cards without the Q).|
