hondo717: |CP||AT|We will discuss the auction in a while, but I think the play is important too. I think you forgot to plan the hand out at trick one angela. You should count out your winners and losers.  You have 1 spade loser, 1 diamond loser, ostensibly. However, the hand is a bit trickier than that, so you need to count your winners as well. You have 4 spade tricks, 3 clubs, 1 diamond, and 1 heart. Therefore, if you ruff 1 heart in dummy, you will come to 10 tricks, because you will score an extra trump trick.|
PG| ***** 87 ***** |


NT|^B@2|CP|8|AT|
hondo717: |CP||AT|Basically, if you play ace of hearts and ruff a heart, you can then draw trumps and claim 10 tricks, losing a trump and 2 hearts. The diamond loser goes on the last club. It comes down to counting your winners and losers at trick one. You still can make it even with the heart finesse losing. The most important thing to learn from this hand is planning at trick one. if you can train yourself to do that, your declarer play will improve immensely.|
