hondo717: |CP||AT|Now, a few things to discuss. First my 3@S bid.  If partner opens a weak 2, and you have 3 card support, it is not dangerous for you to raise to 3, even with few points. Remember, you have a 9 card fit, and it is ok to compete to the 3 level with a 9 card fit. It is only a question of tactics. In this case, I might be afraid of pushing them into a makeable 4@h game, so pass might work out better than 3@S, not because 3@S is dangerous per se, but because it might get us a  bad result. kia probably would pass 3@H if I did not bid 3@s.|
