hondo717: |CP||AT|First the bidding. To answer kia's question, your 2N was a bit risky, as I might make a negative double with as little as 8 points or so, or even less with a long major. However, with 18 points, you would bid 3N, not 2N. As to the play, you do have entry problems in setting up your diamonds. First, you should count your tricks. 3 clubs probably, 2 diamonds at least, and 4 diamonds if they break 3-3,  one heart at least, and no spades. So if only 2 diamonds, you need to take 2 more tricks somewhere. One possibility is an extra heart or two.|
